From Chiba, Japan.

I like traveling around the world and meeting up new people, because I can get to know a lot things from them. I have been to Singapore, Malaysia, Australia, Canada, America, Korea, Denmark, Netherlands, Germany, England, France, Belgium, Taiwan, Cambodia.

Also I like welcoming people from all over the world, because I would like to tell them how Japanese culture is interesting and to provide them to have good experience in Japan.

My interest is circular-economy, eco-friendly, sustainability, SDGs, co-economy, sharing-economy, co-living, co-working, communication, design, architecture, art, culture, food, Japanese tradition, music, etc.

column5:
Hi there! I am Naomasa,an architect.
Grape's NAGAYA is one of my architecture works.This small hotel was built in 2017!
My house is in an area called Kyojima where you can catch a train to Asakusa in 6 mins,or to Tokyo Tower which is known as the tallest tower in Japan in only 2 mins.
Following I am going to present my favorite Kyojima area more bit. This area is quite close to core parts of Tokyo yet differ from other modern streets,Kyojima has its own style and very unique!
About this Kyojima town,there is an old story. 
Once upon a time, the general of the Edo period used to visited this town to see the Japanese garden, watch cherry blossoms, and hunt the birds.Which made this place full of traditional Japanese features. 
There is an old Japanese style of life here, such as the wooden houses,the winding narrow roads,the unique foods.and the friendly neighborhoods who feel like knowing each other for a long time.When you go to the shops, you will meet the lovely and friendly neighborhoods. 
I recommend the shopping street "Kirakira-Shotengai". 
There are many unique shops here selling local food,which may surprise you. 
I prepared an original map which contains some only-local-people-knew restaurants and historical sights.I made it in English.Hope you like it. 


大家好,我是金谷直政｡是一名建筑师｡
这栋小小的酒店｢葡萄的长屋｣(Grape's NAGAYA)是我在2017年自己亲手设计打造建成的｡
坐电车到浅草6分钟,到东京晴空塔2分钟,这里是被称为京岛的街道｡
请允许我向大家介绍一下｡京岛离东京的中心虽然非常近,但并不是像一般的市中心那样到处矗立着现代化的高楼大厦｡
这片区域在以前是江户时代的将军经常来访,参观日本的庭园､赏樱､狩猎的地方｡
木造的住宅,曲折狭小的的通道,独特的食物,还有日常朝夕相处互相理解互相关照的近邻｡
就算是现在也能感受到这种浓浓的温馨氛围｡如果您有时间去到附近的商店,我觉得您会在很大几率上会遇到非常亲切且很棒的当地人｡
特别推荐｢KIRAKIRA商店街｣｡有很多卖着独特食材的特色小店｡相信一定会让您大吃一惊｡
另外我还为您准备了记载着只有当地人知道的食堂､历史､观光地的地图｡
我非常期待与您能够马上见面｡


안녕하세요 저는 카나야 나오마사입니다. 건축가로 일하고 있습니다.
작은 호텔"포도의 숙소"(Grape's NAGAYA)는 제가 디자인 하고 2017년에 완공되었습니다!
이곳은 아사쿠사까지 전차로 6분 도쿄 스카이 트리(일본에서 가장 높은 타워)까지 2분 쿄지마라는 지역입니다.
제가 좋아하는 멋진 쿄지마에 대해서 소개합니다.쿄지마는 도쿄의 중심에 가깝지만 어디에나 있는 현대적인 거리는 아닙니다.

이 지역은 과거에는 에도 시대의 장군이 방문해서, 일본의 정원을 보거나, 벚꽃을 보거나,새를 사냥하했던 지역입니다.
목조 주택, 좁고 구불구불한 길,독특한 음식,그리고 오랫동안 서로를 알고 지냈던 기분이 드는 옛날 일본 스타일이 있습니다.
가게에 가면 멋지고 친근한 사람들을 만날 수 있을겁니다.

특히 쇼핑거리"키라키라 상가"를 추천합니다.현지의 식재료를 파는 독특한 가게가 많이 있습니다.
당신을 놀라게 할지도 모릅니다.
현지의 사람만이 알고 있는 식당과 역사적 명소가 포함되어 있는 오리지날의 지도를 준비했습니다.
하루 빨리 여러분과 만나고 싶습니다.


こんにちは､私は金谷直政です｡建築家として働いています｡
小さなﾎﾃﾙ｢葡萄の長屋｣(Grape's NAGAYA)は自分でﾃﾞｻﾞｲﾝしまし2017年に建てました!
ここは､浅草(浅草)まで電車で6分､東京ｽｶｲﾂﾘｰ(日本で一番高いﾀﾜｰ)まで2分､京島という町になります｡
私の大好きな素敵な京島について紹介します｡京島は東京の中心に近いですが､どこにでもあるような近代的な街にはなっていません｡
この地域は､かつては江戸時代の将軍が訪れ､日本の庭園を見たり､桜を見たり､鳥を狩ったりしていましたｴﾘｱです｡
木造住宅､狭い曲がりくねった道､ﾕﾆｰｸな食べ物､そして長い間お互いを知り合っているような気持ちのある人たちのような古い日本のｽﾀｲﾙがあります｡お店に行くと素敵で親しみやすい人たちに出会うことができると思います｡
特に､ｼｮｯﾋﾟﾝｸﾞ街｢ｷﾗｷﾗ商店街｣をお勧めします｡地元の食材を売っているﾕﾆｰｸなお店がたくさんあります｡あなたを驚かせるかもしれません｡
地元の人だけが知っている食堂や歴史的な名所が含まれているｵﾘｼﾞﾅﾙの地図を用意しました｡
すぐにあなたに会いたいと願っています

こんにちは､私は金谷直政です｡建築家として働いています｡
小さなﾎﾃﾙ｢葡萄の長屋｣(Grape's NAGAYA)は自分でﾃﾞｻﾞｲﾝしまし2017年に建てました!
ここは､浅草(浅草)まで電車で6分､東京ｽｶｲﾂﾘｰ(日本で一番高いﾀﾜｰ)まで2分､京島という町になります｡
私の大好きな素敵な京島について紹介します｡京島は東京の中心に近いですが､どこにでもあるような近代的な街にはなっていません｡
この地域は､かつては江戸時代の将軍が訪れ､日本の庭園を見たり､桜を見たり､鳥を狩ったりしていましたｴﾘｱです｡
木造住宅､狭い曲がりくねった道､ﾕﾆｰｸな食べ物､そして長い間お互いを知り合っているような気持ちのある人たちのような古い日本のｽﾀｲﾙがあります｡お店に行くと素敵で親しみやすい人たちに出会うことができると思います｡
特に､ｼｮｯﾋﾟﾝｸﾞ街｢ｷﾗｷﾗ商店街｣をお勧めします｡地元の食材を売っているﾕﾆｰｸなお店がたくさんあります｡あなたを驚かせるかもしれません｡
地元の人だけが知っている食堂や歴史的な名所が含まれているｵﾘｼﾞﾅﾙの地図を用意しました｡
すぐにあなたに会いたいと願っています

column5:
Hi there! I am Naomasa,an architect.
Grape's NAGAYA is one of my architecture works.This small hotel was built in 2017!
My house is in an area called Kyojima where you can catch a train to Asakusa in 6 mins,or to Tokyo Tower which is known as the tallest tower in Japan in only 2 mins.
Following I am going to present my favorite Kyojima area more bit. This area is quite close to core parts of Tokyo yet differ from other modern streets,Kyojima has its own style and very unique!
About this Kyojima town,there is an old story. 
Once upon a time, the general of the Edo period used to visited this town to see the Japanese garden, watch cherry blossoms, and hunt the birds.Which made this place full of traditional Japanese features. 
There is an old Japanese style of life here, such as the wooden houses,the winding narrow roads,the unique foods.and the friendly neighborhoods who feel like knowing each other for a long time.When you go to the shops, you will meet the lovely and friendly neighborhoods. 
I recommend the shopping street "Kirakira-Shotengai". 
There are many unique shops here selling local food,which may surprise you. 
I prepared an original map which contains some only-local-people-knew restaurants and historical sights.I made it in English.Hope you like it. 


大家好,我是金谷直政｡是一名建筑师｡
这栋小小的酒店｢葡萄的长屋｣(Grape's NAGAYA)是我在2017年自己亲手设计打造建成的｡
坐电车到浅草6分钟,到东京晴空塔2分钟,这里是被称为京岛的街道｡
请允许我向大家介绍一下｡京岛离东京的中心虽然非常近,但并不是像一般的市中心那样到处矗立着现代化的高楼大厦｡
这片区域在以前是江户时代的将军经常来访,参观日本的庭园､赏樱､狩猎的地方｡
木造的住宅,曲折狭小的的通道,独特的食物,还有日常朝夕相处互相理解互相关照的近邻｡
就算是现在也能感受到这种浓浓的温馨氛围｡如果您有时间去到附近的商店,我觉得您会在很大几率上会遇到非常亲切且很棒的当地人｡
特别推荐｢KIRAKIRA商店街｣｡有很多卖着独特食材的特色小店｡相信一定会让您大吃一惊｡
另外我还为您准备了记载着只有当地人知道的食堂､历史､观光地的地图｡
我非常期待与您能够马上见面｡


안녕하세요 저는 카나야 나오마사입니다. 건축가로 일하고 있습니다.
작은 호텔"포도의 숙소"(Grape's NAGAYA)는 제가 디자인 하고 2017년에 완공되었습니다!
이곳은 아사쿠사까지 전차로 6분 도쿄 스카이 트리(일본에서 가장 높은 타워)까지 2분 쿄지마라는 지역입니다.
제가 좋아하는 멋진 쿄지마에 대해서 소개합니다.쿄지마는 도쿄의 중심에 가깝지만 어디에나 있는 현대적인 거리는 아닙니다.

이 지역은 과거에는 에도 시대의 장군이 방문해서, 일본의 정원을 보거나, 벚꽃을 보거나,새를 사냥하했던 지역입니다.
목조 주택, 좁고 구불구불한 길,독특한 음식,그리고 오랫동안 서로를 알고 지냈던 기분이 드는 옛날 일본 스타일이 있습니다.
가게에 가면 멋지고 친근한 사람들을 만날 수 있을겁니다.

특히 쇼핑거리"키라키라 상가"를 추천합니다.현지의 식재료를 파는 독특한 가게가 많이 있습니다.
당신을 놀라게 할지도 모릅니다.
현지의 사람만이 알고 있는 식당과 역사적 명소가 포함되어 있는 오리지날의 지도를 준비했습니다.
하루 빨리 여러분과 만나고 싶습니다.

Hi there, My name is Ai. I live in Tokyo with my family. I am an interpreter and my husband has his own business. I am Japanese and he is American. 

We both have lived in many countries - U.S., Canada and Vietnam - and have enjoyed traveling to more than 20 countries globally. :-) We are foodies and love good restaurants and great wine. You can definitely find great food in Tokyo, from Japanese (obviously) to French and Italian. Did you know that Tokyo have more Michelin starred restaurants than Paris?

Tokyo is a great city, with awesome food and bustling nightlife. 

We can speak in English, Japanese, French and Vietnamese. Let us know if you have any questions about Tokyo and Japan. 

Sincerely,
Ai

We all were born in Tokyo and live here for a long time. We love this city and would like to introdue this attractive city to the all guest!
Our family ourselves loves to travel all over the world. And we also love to meet people with different countries and be interested in learning about their culture, as well!

We've just started to host at our apartment and happy to support your comfortable stay. If you have any concern to visit to Japan, please ask me freely. 
We'll do our best during your stay! We're looking forward to your reservations!!
Tokyo is one of the most beautiful and attractive city in the world. 
I’m sure you’ll enjoy your stay!

こんにちは satsukiです｡
仕事ではﾌﾟﾛﾓｰｼｮﾝ会社を12年経営しています｡
家族は､妻と女の子が2人です｡
毎日､家族和気あいあいと楽しく過ごしています!

旅行が好きで､学生の頃は､東南ｱｼﾞｱをﾊﾞｯｸﾊﾟｯｶｰで回りました｡

今は､おしゃれな空間で過ごすのが好きで､AirBnBで東京に来る旅行者の皆様にも良い空間で東京生活を過ごしてもらいたくて､この部屋を作りました｡

錦糸町は東京のﾒｲﾝｽﾎﾟｯﾄへのｱｸｾｽも抜群で､なんと言っても東京のｼﾝﾎﾞﾙの東京ｽｶｲﾂﾘｰまで電車で2分という好立地な場所です｡
旅行者の皆様にとってもかなり利便性が高いと思います｡

僕の趣味はｱｲｽﾎｯｹｰやﾌｯﾄｻﾙなどのｽﾎﾟｰﾄをすることと､お酒を飲みながら楽しく喋ることです｡
この部屋と私の家も近いので､ﾀｲﾐﾝｸﾞが合えば､一緒にお酒でも飲めたら嬉しいです!

Hello! We are Khaosan Tokyo Laboratory, a cozy hostel in Asakusa:)
Thank you for stopping by.

We are located at Asakusa, easy access from any stations there.

･5 minutes walk from “Exit 3” of Tawaramachi station on Ginza line (ﾒﾄﾛ銀座線田原町駅)
･13 minutes walk from “Exit A4” of Asakusa station on Toei Asakusa line (都営浅草線浅草駅)
･5 minutes walk from “Exit 4” of Asakusa station on Tsukuba Express (つくばｴｸｽﾌﾟﾚｽ浅草駅).

･1,290Yen / 80min from Narita Airport (成田空港)
･620Yen / 45min from Haneda Airport (羽田空港)

Asakusa is perfect for travelling Tokyo. Of course it is walking-distance to go to Sensoji Temple (浅草寺/せんそうじ) and Kaminarimon (雷門/かみなりもん).

Our unique colourful rooms are perfect for 3-4 people groups, and families!:)

We hope to see you soon at our hostel!
If you have any inquiries, feel free to contact us:)

column5:
Hello, We are Chiliko. We live in the heart of Tokyo.

This is a picture of me and my friends where we will try to accommodate you in our best way we can. If you've never come to Tokyo, I'd say you need to come to explore this rich culture at least once in your lifetime! Bring back some of this strong and full energy back to your country with you! If you have been in Tokyo before or heading back again, I say you should come stay with us to feel our genuine services we offer to make everyone feels like having a travelling guardian angel to assist you in every way throughout your trip! We want you to have the same touchy feelings as we do!

We are looking forward to hear more from you.

Best,
-Chiliko Nishi

//////////////////////////////////////////////////

您好,我們是Chiliko!我們來自台灣,香港,和日本~現在都居住在東京市中心附近｡
每個人一定要來過東京一趟感受一下它濃厚的文化氣息和熱鬧繁忙街上穿插的寧靜小巷以及街上攤販叫賣活力,您一定會愛上這座城市的!如果您已經來過東京,那我們希望您能來體驗感受我們真心誠摯的服務品質,增添您旅程其中一個美好的回憶之一~

我們非常期待您的到來喔!

//////////////////////////////////////////////////

column6:
Hi everyone my name is Shinju.
 I love travelling and exploring new cultures.
Since I was a child I used to travel abroad to improve my English, I used to live in the U.K. where I became very passionate about Europe and its art and history, little by little I start travelling also around Asia and US.
I had the opportunity to get in touch with different people from all over the world, that’s why I have started hosting to keep getting in touch with many people from different countries!
I now work in Tokyo as an s/e of IT industry. I know this city pretty well, so I can suggest you many spots and things to do and enjoy of this city!
I hope you will have a wonderful holiday in my country and make incredible memories!

I'd love to introduce my host friends, Azuki and Maki and Hatsuko! They own apartments in Shinjuku and Shibuya area.
Take a look at their lovely rooms!
Azuki - https://www.airbnb.jp/users/show/ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) Maki - https://www.airbnb.jp/users/show/ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) Hatsuko - https://www.airbnb.jp/users/show/ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) Hope your stay will be a wonderful one:)
Thank you,
Shinju

Hello Everybody!
I’m Takada, 
I was born and raised in Tokyo so I know this city pretty well!
I love travelling, and trying all local foods and interact with the locals.
When I was in junior high school I did exchange student vacation in Pennsylvania
I loved living abroad, every time I have the possibility I try to travel as much as I can!
I wish I can visit at least half of this world and make friends from any part of the globe!
I now work in advertisement in Tokyo, I play guitar in my spare time and listen to music pretty all much of the time!
Please feel free to contact me anytime you want I will be more than happy to assist you!
I can give you advices about good spot in to visit in Japan, and about delicious foods to try while you are in my country.
Let’s make your journey in my city a memorable experience!

Thank you for taking the time to read my profile. Bai

column11:
This is a special big family, the members of this family are from all around the world gathering in Tokyo 時の家 guest house. 

I'm an IT engineer who loves to explore different cultures. I've been to 11 countries such as the United States,  Germany, Australia, and India. Having you all at my home is another way to understand the world more:).

column6:
Hello, I'm Ken.

I live in Tokyo and born and raised there.

My hobby is watch football games and comedy on TV and watch movies.

I talk with people, love to connect people and people.
I founded the company.Airbnb is the main company business.

Through this business I wanna to make a community where people from all over the world are connected by Japan.

Please enjoy a nice stay in Japan.

=========================

Hi there! I'm Non:)

I enjoy talking to all kind of people!
Since I've learnt English in US and the UK, my world changed a lot. My personality turned into out going, talkative, and a fun lover!:D
Now I'm working as a freelancer for my English skills, outdoor skills, and helping handicap people.
In my free time, I enjoy playing foot ball (soccer), snow boarding, and surfing!

Some time I organize international parties for fun! 
It's nice because I can see my friends around and meet new  people from the world at the same time!

In the future, I want to keep connecting the world :)

Hi everyone my name is kasa.
 I love travelling and exploring new cultures.
Since I was a child I used to travel abroad to improve my English, I used to live in the U.K. where I became very passionate about Europe and its art and history, little by little I start travelling also around Asia and US.
I had the opportunity to get in touch with different people from all over the world, that’s why I have started hosting to keep getting in touch with many people from different countries!
I now work in Tokyo as an s/e of IT industry. I know this city pretty well, so I can suggest you many spots and things to do and enjoy of this city!
I hope you will have a wonderful holiday in my country and make incredible memories!

I'd love to introduce my host friends, Hinata and Takada! They own apartments in Tokyo area.
Take a look at their lovely rooms!
Hinata - https://www.airbnb.jp/users/show/ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) Takada - https://www.airbnb.jp/users/show/ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) I met a beautiful girl while studying at uni. Her name is Nao and also hosts on airbnb. Her rooms are as lovely as my 2 friends' above!
https://www.airbnb.jp/users/show/ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) Hope your stay will be a wonderful one:)
Thank you,
Kasa

Hello Everybody!
I’m Takada, 
I was born and raised in Tokyo so I know this city pretty well!
I love travelling, and trying all local foods and interact with the locals.
When I was in junior high school I did exchange student vacation in Pennsylvania
I loved living abroad, every time I have the possibility I try to travel as much as I can!
I wish I can visit at least half of this world and make friends from any part of the globe!
I now work in advertisement in Tokyo, I play guitar in my spare time and listen to music pretty all much of the time!
Please feel free to contact me anytime you want I will be more than happy to assist you!
I can give you advices about good spot in to visit in Japan, and about delicious foods to try while you are in my country.
Let’s make your journey in my city a memorable experience!


Takada

column4:
Hi! Nice to meet you.
We're a mother-daughter team currently living in Tokyo and love sharing our recommendations and tips to travelers. Don't hesitate to ask us any questions. Together we can speak English, Japanese and Chinese.

Mikoto & Cassandra

Hello everyone! My name is Kanako.
I am 25 years old, working at a cafe in Tokyo. 
I've been living in Tokyo for 15 years and used to live in the U.S for several years.
I went to the land of liberty to be a great dancer.
Dance has been a great part of my life. 
At the age of 18, I chose to go overseas all by myself to change my life.
It certainly did.
I stayed at host family's place while in the U.S and I loved it when the host mother made me a pancake for breakfast with a cup of coffee. 
They treated me like a real family and I felt their warmth and kindness on my skin.
It wasn’t dance but their hospitality that changed my life!

I started hosting on Airbnb after I came back here to Japan.
I was hoping that I could do the same like the host family did to me :)
Now that the word ‘hosting’ stands for something different in Japan now from what I remember, I’d love to hang out with as many of you as I can!
I’m working until night but quick response is promised.
 
Let’s make your holiday a wonderful one together!

Thank you,
Kanako

Hi everyone my name is Shotaro.
 I love travelling and exploring new cultures.
Since I was a child I used to travel abroad to improve my English, I used to live in the U.K. where I became very passionate about Europe and its art and history, little by little I start travelling also around Asia and US.
I had the opportunity to get in touch with different people from all over the world, that’s why I have started hosting to keep getting in touch with many people from different countries!
I now work in Tokyo as an s/e of IT industry. I know this city pretty well, so I can suggest you many spots and things to do and enjoy of this city!
I hope you will have a wonderful holiday in my country and make incredible memories!

Foreign visitors who do not have domestic addresses in Japan must provide the photo of passport front page. ※ 日本政府が定めた法律に基づき､宿泊者の氏名､住所､職業及び連絡先の提供｡日本国内に住所を有していない外国人観光客である時は､その国籍及び旅行番号の提示を求める｡旅券の写しを宿泊者名簿と共に保存すること｡ ※ 日本政府制定的法律规定,要求民宿住宿者提供姓名,住址,职业及联系方式｡没有日本国内住址的外国游客,务必提供国籍和护照号码｡将护照的复印件住宿者名单一起保存｡ ※ﾍﾞｯﾄﾞでの飲食はお控えください｡ ※PM10時以降はお静かに過ごしてください｡洗濯などもお控えください｡ ※一人旅のお客様はご利用できません｡ ※ｺﾞﾐはｺﾞﾐ箱までお捨てください｡ ※ﾌﾛｰﾘﾝｸﾞ､ｶｰﾍﾞｯﾄﾞ､芝生､寝具にはｶﾞﾑを捨てないでください｡発覚次第､ｸﾘｰﾆﾝｸﾞ代として1万円頂戴します｡ ※電気とｸｰﾗｰを消してからお出かけください｡ ※幼児の就寝時はおむつを付けてください｡それ以外の対策もあればご協力ください｡ ※ｷｯﾁﾝ用品の使用後は必ず清掃を行って下さい｡ﾁｪｯｸｱｳﾄ時､未清掃のもの発見次第､ｸﾘｰﾆﾝｸﾞ代として3000円頂戴します｡ ※宿泊者以外の訪問及び宿泊はご遠慮ください｡予約外のお客様がいらした場合､一日につき一人1万円頂戴します｡ 谢谢你选择我的房源,请把它当成您在东京的家｡ 我们会用心为您准备一个整洁,舒适的环境｡ *请不要在床上饮食 *晚上22点以后请不要大声喧哗,请不要洗衣服｡ *不接受一个人旅游｡ *垃圾请丢入垃圾箱｡ *不要在地板,地毯,草坪,寝具上吐口香糖｡发现追加清洁费用一万日币｡ *出门请关闭电灯,空调｡ *婴幼儿睡觉请穿好纸尿裤并做好相关防护｡ *厨房用具使用过后请清洗干净,退房时,用具未洗刷的情况,清洁费用追加3000日币｡ *不接

column5:
Hi, I'm Kunihiko  (I know it's long, so everyone calls me kuni.) I had lived in the u.s. for five years, and now I am a happy dad with lovely wife, two handful boys.

My wife and I met in the U.s., and we are passionate about meeting with new people. We also love to visit new places, and discover fun local information such as great dinings, shops, and cultures in town.
I would be more than happy to share those information with you, and make your special trip as pleasant as possible.

Tokyo is a very attractive city;  a mixture of new modern and traditional cultures, and each town has unique own culture. 

I know as a traveler, you would want to see many places and experience various things to explore japanese culture. 

Let our place be part of your precious trip to explore, have fun, and give you comfort.  If you ever need our help, we are there to help you in either english or of course, in japanese.

Please feel free to contact me for any questions you may have.

Hope to hear from you soon, and we are looking forward to meeting with you (at least one time when i hand you the key!)

column6:
Hi everyone, my name is Shingo!
I love travelling and exploring new cultures.
Since I was a child I used to travel abroad to improve my English, I used to live in the U.K. where I became very passionate about Europe and its art and history, little by little I start travelling also around Asia and US.
I had the opportunity to get in touch with different people from all over the world, that’s why I have started hosting to keep getting in touch with many people from different countries!
I now work in Tokyo as an s/e of IT industry. I know this city pretty well, so I can suggest you many spots and things to do and enjoy of this city!
I hope you will have a wonderful holiday in my country and make incredible memories!

Hi I'm Sayaka.
Thank you for visiting my page.

As for myself, my hobbies are playing sports(especially tennis and volleyball), watching sports(ice hockey), riding horses, and traveling.

A: There are several conditions for early check-in and late checkout. Early check-in (from 2PM (14:00) Japan Time) and Late check-out (till 1:30PM (13:30) Japan Time) may be available under 4 conditions below: a) There is no prior guest nor next guest on the same day of your arrival or check-out day. b) We require you of paying an extra cost for each extension. c) We can manage your early check-in or late check-out. d) Such extra charge is confirmed on Airbnb. AND PLACE is a subsidiary owned and operated by Plays Inc. in Tokyo, Japan since 2015.

Services include managing private lodging listings in various languages including English, Japanese, Chinese, French, Spanish and Tagalog.

Our multi-lingual customer service department provides customer support to both house owners and guests who stay at our establishments. The houses available range from small apartments that can house at least 2 people to large 3 floor houses that can accommodate more than 24 guests. We also have houses and apartments that are wheelchair friendly. We also accommodate longer-term stays for guests who would like to stay for more than a month. Guests who plan to book for multiple months can contact us with their specific details and requirements regarding their accommodation needs.

Please feel free to contact us here via the airbnb platform for further enquiries regarding all our airbnb listings.

来日12年｡喜欢东京这个城市｡也希望来日旅游的各位都和我一样喜欢这里!

column2: How to access and check in? We will provide Access information as PDF after we receive your travel information. We will send Check-in/out information as PDF 2 days before your arrival day. We will send code to check in at around 3 pm on your arrival day.

FAQs Q: How can I reach your place from the airport? A: Various transportation methods exist for accessing my place from Narita and Haneda Airports. AND PLACE is a subsidiary owned and operated by Plays Inc. in Tokyo, Japan since 2015.

Services include managing private lodging listings in various languages including English, Japanese, Chinese, French, Spanish and Tagalog.

Our multi-lingual customer service department provides customer support to both house owners and guests who stay at our establishments. The houses available range from small apartments that can house at least 2 people to large 3 floor houses that can accommodate more than 24 guests. We also have houses and apartments that are wheelchair friendly. We also accommodate longer-term stays for guests who would like to stay for more than a month. Guests who plan to book for multiple months can contact us with their specific details and requirements regarding their accommodation needs.

Please feel free to contact us here via the airbnb platform for further enquiries regarding all our airbnb listings.

column4:
Hi I'm Sayaka.
Thank you for visiting my page.

As for myself, my hobbies are playing sports(especially tennis and volleyball), watching sports(ice hockey), riding horses, and traveling.
Until now I've been to Australia, Canada, US, UK, Netherlands, Germany, Switzerland, Liechtenstein, Italy, Monaco, France, Peru, Bolivia, Korea, Taiwan and Malaysia. (hope I didn't miss any...)
I also enjoy traveling around Japan from northern Hokkaindo to southern Okinawa.
Let us know if you need some help with your destinations/activities while you stay here ;) 

Also, I would be more than happy to meet you in person and spend some time talking/eating/drinking with you if you would like. (I could invite my friends as well; the more the merrier...!)
Look forward to see you in Tokyo anyway ;)

column5:
Hello!
We are Chinese ladies living in Japan and China.

We have a beautiful house in Asakusa area where you can find fascinating Japanese culture such as quaint atmosphere Asakusa and new landmark Skytree.

In Asakusa, you can rent out and try putting on Kimono casually for strolling, and it will be your great experience!

The entire city is the special shooting spot, so you can definitely enjoy every pictures you take for your memories.

At Skytree, you’ll be amazed by the panoramic Tokyo view from the observatory, and can find your favorite souvenir including Pokemon goods. There are also aquarium and many gift shops, where you’ll see whole entertainment for all ages!

There are many more to see!
In Asakusa area, where our house is located, you’ll have good transportation and great access to other famous tourist spots. 
(No train transfer needed from both Narita and Haneda airport!)

We would like to share with you the best experience of the wonderful Japanese cuisines, culture, nature, and subculture that Japan has.

Please let us be your friend for any advice, and we’ll help you to make your Japan trip very special!

column17:
Hey everyone - ようこそ! 

Thanks for checking out our page! I am Yu. Not You, that would be confusing! haha


I have a lovely family and I have lived in Tokyo all my life.  I work a steady 9-5 job but I love travel and I love my city, so I decided to offer guests a great Tokyo experience on Airbnb. 

Tokyo is the worlds most populous metropolis, yet our apartments are designed to make you feel like you never left the comfort of your own home. The apartments have a traditional Japanese feel. After all, you are traveling in Japan. :)

My town is in the older, traditional section of old “Edo” (what Tokyo used to be called long ago). Nearby, you can visit the tallest free standing structure in all of Japan, Tokyo Skytree. From there you can see great distances, including Fuji-san (Mt Fuji) on a clear day.


Thanks again for looking. Feel free to drop us a message at anytime with any Tokyo related questions you may have. We’re always happy to help out. 

☺ Kampai! ☺

Life motto is “Do not take the road everyone else takes, for it will only get you stuck in traffic.”

ps凌晨12:00~早上7:00有联系不到我们的可能性(不小心睡着了...zZ),所以有问题的话,请务必提前告知哦｡
大家好!我们是一群热爱旅游,更热爱分享的中国小伙伴,因为喜欢东京而聚集成了一个团队,叫做宅东｡
我们从日本民宿法正式颁布开始,便在东京的人气旅游地开启了合法民宿房东之旅!
我们经营的大多数民宿都位于东京新地标——Skytree晴空塔附近,为何选择晴空塔?因为东京晴空塔不只是座塔!这里其实被称为晴空镇,有购物商场､餐厅､水族馆､天文馆及博物馆｡在这里你会看到很多日本人,因为他们知道不用去游客聚集的新宿银座涩谷,就在东京晴空塔,吃喝玩乐也都可一网打尽!
其次呢,这里也靠近非常著名的浅草寺~无论是樱花季步行到附近的隅田川赏樱,还是夏日在民宿的屋顶就能观赏隅田川的花火大会,都是旅行中非常惬意的体验!
而且啊,这里也靠近可以直达两大机场的地铁站【押上】,完全不用在东京复杂的地铁站里迷路哟~
我们的民宿都是全新日式装修,大多数民宿配有冰箱､洗衣机､电磁炉､微波炉等常用设备,浴室洗手间干湿分离,采用智能密码锁,24小时自助入住,入住便利又安心; 房间也非常干净,这一切都希望能在日本能够给您“家的感觉”!

Hello everyone! We are a group of Chinese friends who love to travel and share more. We love Tokyo and have gathered together to form a team called ZAITO.
Since the official promulgation  we have begun a legal homestay landlord tour around the popular tourist destination in Tokyo!
Most of our homestays are located near Tokyo's new landmark——Tokyo Skytree. 
Why choose Skytree? Because Tokyo Skytree is more than just a tower! It's actually called Skytree Town, which with shopping malls, restaurants, aquariums, planetariums, and museums. You will see a lot of Japanese here because they know that they don’t have to go to the Shinjuku/Ginza/Shibuya, which is where tourists gather. They are right at the Tokyo Skytree, and they can eat, drink, and play all at once!
Secondly, it is also close to the famous Sensoji Temple ~ Whether it is walking to the nearby Sumida River in the cherry blossom season, or you can watch the Sumida River Fireworks Festival on the roof of the homestay in summer, it's a very pleasant experience during the trip!
Moreover, here is also close to the Metro station 【Oshiage】, which has direct access to the 2 airports(NRT/HND), so you don't have to get lost in the complicated metro in Tokyo ~
Our homestays are all newly decorated in Japanese style. Most homestays are equipped with refrigerators, washing machines, induction cookers, microwave ovens, and other common equipment. The bathrooms are separated from the wet and dry, using electric code locks, 24H self-check-in, Clean, all these hope to give you a "feel at home"experience in Japan!

AND PLACE is a subsidiary owned and operated by Plays Inc. in Tokyo, Japan since 2015.

Services include managing private lodging listings in various languages including English, Japanese, Chinese, French, Spanish and Tagalog.

Our multi-lingual customer service department provides customer support to both house owners and guests who stay at our establishments. The houses available range from small apartments that can house at least 2 people to large 3 floor houses that can accommodate more than 24 guests. We also have houses and apartments that are wheelchair friendly. We also accommodate longer-term stays for guests who would like to stay for more than a month. Guests who plan to book for multiple months can contact us with their specific details and requirements regarding their accommodation needs.

Please feel free to contact us here via the airbnb platform for further enquiries regarding all our airbnb listings.

column4:
Hello, I’m Nomad!
Nomad’s listings are run by MATSUDO Corporation, and we manage, operate and deal with guests. 
We have been welcoming guests from all over the world since March in 2016. 
 
We have English speaking staff, so feel free to contact us if you have any inquiries!

We’re not only offering places to stay but we more value on ‘Interaction’ and ‘Experience’ with our guests. 
We’re doing our best to hospitalize our guests and share ‘a once-in-a lifetime’ experience. 
There is also our Information desk at an old Japanese-style House, Harada Rice Shop, and we are offering information about the area and various services. 
Feel free to stop by if you need anything!
We’ll have some events to get together sometimes!
We’re looking forward to meeting you in Japan!

こんにちは､NOMADです｡
NOMADの民泊施設は株式会社MATSUDOが直営でｹﾞｽﾄ対応､施設の管理･運営をしています｡
2016年3月よりｽﾀｰﾄし､世界中からたくさんのｹﾞｽﾄをお迎えしています｡

私たちは単に民泊施設を提供するだけではなく､世界中の様々な国から日本を訪れたｹﾞｽﾄとの｢交流｣や｢体験｣を大切にしています｡
私達の民泊施設を選んでくださったｹﾞｽﾄの皆様との一期一会を大切に､最高のおもてなしができるよう､努力してまいります｡
